reviews.text: Installed correctly myself but when turning light on, lights would flicker. Got concerned about this so ordered a switch from a different company and hired an electrician to come out. He confirmed this Leviton switch was a defect and no matter how tightly the screws are fastened, there is an internal fault that causes flickering. Looks like I need to file a warranty claim for this thing now. Really annoying as I had to hire an electrician to confirm what I already suspected. I have used Leviton switches before and they worked fine, but it’s very frustrating to get a bad one.

reviews.text: I don't understand why electrical devices that just a few years ago were 'cheap' are not >5x the price. This one is a standard 4way switch. It works fine, but I feel like a chump for paying the full price for it. Feels unethical to charge this much for a simple light switch. Also, as others stated, the switch action is a bit stiff and loud. I didn't think it would matter to me until I put it in the wall and have to actually concentrate when flipping the switch, to apply extra pressure to make it 'pop'. Strange that it's so stiff. And again, if I hadn't spent the same amount of $$ on it as a nice meal in a restaurant, I wouldn't be so picky :)

reviews.productTitle: Leviton 5604-2W 15 Amp, 120/277 Volt, Decora Rocker 4-Way AC Quiet Switch, Residential Grade, Grounding, White
reviews.text: The switch delivered from Amazon was of surprisingly poor quality. I have installed well over 1,000 Leviton switches over the years. Depending on the grade of switch, they have all installed and performed as expected. The switch that was delivered had two terminal bolts that were installed at an angle, and when partially backed out showed stripping of the threads. The switch casing was also slightly skewed, making it hard to fit into a standard plate. As I needed to get the job done, I took terminal bolts from another switch and, with considerable effort, got them to seat in the internal square nuts. A bit of careful trimming with a utility knife got the faceplate on. I hope this doesn’t reflect a decrease in quality of Leviton’s switches. Despite becoming lighter and a bit more flimsy over the years, they have remained reliable.
reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on February 14, 2021
reviews.title: Surprisingly poor quality

reviews.text: I installed a number of Leviton single-pole switches, and I like them, but the feel of this quiet switch is rather mushy. It's not a big deal as it works well enough. What was frustrating was the stripped threads on one of the nuts. When I began to install it, I noticed one of the screws was in, so I began to unscrew it, and it was extremely tight. I succeeded after a little effort and saw the threads were stripped in the nut. After ten minutes of faffing about, I managed to screw it down well enough that I'd get a good connection that would hold, but if it's unscrewed, the screw will pop out of the nut.
reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2020
reviews.title: Mushy feeling, one of the nuts was stripped

reviews.productTitle: Leviton 5604-2W 15 Amp, 120/277 Volt, Decora Rocker 4-Way AC Quiet Switch, Residential Grade, Grounding, White
reviews.text: The switch I received was clearly used - the green paint on the grounding screw was coming off from where a screwdriver had previously been used on it. The switch also was dirty and worn. Beyond looking worn, the feel of the switch isn't smooth at all and makes inconsistent sounds when engaging. It's just not a good product. All my other (two and three way) switches in the house are Leviton and have been impresive. However, this four way switch was significantly more expensive and is a dud. I don't have time to replace it again but the product was very disappointing. If I could do it again, I'd definitely buy a different switch.
